.TH "_base_mpi_ep_writeq" 9 "_base_mpi_ep_writeq" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_base_mpi_ep_writeq \- 32 bit write to MMIO
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" _base_mpi_ep_writeq
.BI "(__u64 b "  ","
.BI "volatile void __iomem *addr "  ","
.BI "spinlock_t *writeq_lock "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "b" 12
data payload
.IP "addr" 12
address in MMIO space
.IP "writeq_lock" 12
spin lock
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This special handling for MPI EP to take care of 32 bit
environment where its not quarenteed to send the entire word
in one transfer.
